annotationA: Protein binding; glutamate-cysteine ligase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: cellular response to DNA damage stimulus; glutathione metabolic process; glutathione biosynthetic process; Belongs to the glutamate--cysteine ligase type 3 family
annotationB: Gamma-glutamyl transpeptidase (Ggt-1) transfers the gamma-glutamyl moiety from donors to substrates, e.g. transfer to water generates glutamate. Ggt-1 roles include glutathione metabolism, reproduction and light avoidance
